<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-21T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-21T15:00:00-05:00" n="487" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d487">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10615:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-21T21:00:00+01:00">April 21,
                                    1944—9 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received April 21—8:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1397. Department’s 635, April 10, 8 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d487fn1">Same as telegram 861, <ref target="#pg_495">p. 495</ref>.</note>
                            Under instructions from Soviet Government Semenov, Counselor of Soviet
                            Legation here, yesterday called on Boheman and supported American
                            representation regarding immediate cessation of Swedish exports of
                            bearings, bearing machinery, et cetera, and piston rings.</p>
                        <p>In the ensuing conversation Semenov expressed opinion that Sweden has no
                            real reason to fear Germany and that discovery of war maps (Legation’s
                            1317, April 17<note n="24" xml:id="d487fn2">Not printed.</note>) was
                            result of German plant which could only be described as “a cheap
                            bluff”.</p>
                        <p>My 308, April 21, 9 p.m. repeats this to London.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>